<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 4:53PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Stanly
County through 515 PM EDT...
At 453 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Midland, or 15 miles northeast of Monroe, moving west at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fairview In Union County, Locust, Oakboro and Stanfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
